description:
"I was given a second chance in death. Vengeance was offered and I was quick to accept."

A cloaked Stranger slips into the rustic Town of Oasis changing things forever. Ten years it had been since he ran this town with malice and harshness. Even then there was hope for his soul. His wife and daughter were on the verge of turning him from wickedness. But they were murdered, and so was he. He is granted seven days to reap seven souls and gain a chance at revenge. Conflict arises as a young girl (Niobe Ayutami) reminds him of his murdered daughter. She acts as his conscience and become his only hope for salvation.
name: Day 1 of 7

description: Fright anthology containing 7 tales of terror: "Issue Ate", "Thinner and Thinner", "Fifty years going on forever", "Hunger pangs", "Rose", "Interlude", and "Marv"

description: Hot Dog is transported to a dimension of animals, where he has super powers and fights crime.
name: Hot Dog is Bark-Man The Canine Crusader!

description: What happens when the most evil and powerful female characters in the Grimm Universe join forces? You'll find out in this new miniseries that brings together an all star cast of girls that were born to be bad. The Mistress of Limbo has gathered together a team of allies from across the four realms of power. Will anyone be able to stand against the united power of Baba Yaga, the Goblin Queen and the Queen of spades? Don't miss the baddest series in the history of Grimm Fairy Tales.

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales presents Bad Girls

description:
Check out all your favorite fairy tale babes in their sexiest beach wear in the second installment of Zenescope's Grimm Fairy Tales swimsuit issue. This issue is filled with over 25 images, many of them brand new, as well as a never before published back up short story. Includes artwork from Ebas, Mike Debalfo, Billy Tucci and more! Fairy Tales have never looked better than this.

Note: The cover is an homage to Baywatch.
name: The Game

description:
THE 75th ANNIVERSARY ISSUE OF GRIMM FAIRY TALES IS HERE! Sela has finally returned to earth in search of her long lost daughter. It's a search that will lead her to confront the powerful Dark One, the only being who holds the answers to her daughter's location. But when Sela finds her daughter will she be ready for the truth about her? Don't miss this shocking oversized issue that will change everything!

Note: One of the alternate covers is an homage to a recruiting poster featuring Uncle Sam. New York City only appears on an alternate cover.
name: The Return

description: 'The Dark Spiral,' Part 1: 'The Abandoned Witch Village.' An ill wind blows from the rooftops of an abandoned witch village. Evil fairies and a dark queen with wicked intent haunt Tarot as she begins a downward spiral. Issue #75 is the beginning of an epic journey that will change Tarot's life - as well as everyone she loves.
name: The Dark Spiral, Part 1: The Abandoned Witch Village

volume.name: Tarot: Witch of the Black Rose

description: There is a fate worse than death. The most fiendish weapon of all is unleashed by Hitler's maddest scientists: the hideous battalions of Der Totenkorps! They are beyond death, they know no fear, and they only crave the flesh of the living. Now the Allies must stand and fight against the bloodthirsty 'Death Corps', or witness the world devoured alive!
name: Ride To Hell!; Unholy Night

description: The first Smallville arc comes to a cataclysmic close as Clark comes to terms with the aftermath of his battle with the Cyborg Superman. Was it all part of Lex's greater plan to finally get the better of his former friend?
name: Guardian Chapter 12

description: Lovely ladies of steampunk style dare to expose themselves... to all the adventure they can handle! See them romp in their roundabouts or disport in their dirigibles in satin, silk, and lace; to brass-studded denim and leather. These brazen beauties can take the heat - can you?
name: Steam Wars

description:
"Good thing about an alleyway in my home town. You can scream and no one will care."

A Stranger has returned to Oasis. A deal has been made. Seven souls for seven days. Now, he is holed up in a tavern cared for by a girl (Niobe Ayutami) not old enough to remember his past. She radiates an innocence that defies his thirst for vengeance. But there is another soul to collect, and he shall find it within the brutal and blood soaked underbelly of the town: The Pit Fight Arena!
name: Day 2 of 7

description: After the events of the Dream Eater saga, Calie and Violet are on the run from the denizens of Wonderland. But after a lifetime of believing her life to be normal, Violet is slowly coming to terms with the insanity that is her lineage and will finally learn the truth of who and what she really is. This is not to be missed story leads directly into the brand new Wonderland ongoing series and is the perfect jumping on point of new readers.
name: Wonderland 2012 Annual

And even the combined strength of Bomani, Mowglii, and Baloo may not be enough to stop him from devouring them all.

description:
Hilarious, frightening, mysterious, adorable and utterly bleak, Chocolate Cheeks has arrived to disgust and delight comic-book readers of all ages. âSweetâ Chubby Cheeks and the Pullapart Boy (a 21st Century Frankensteinâs monster for kids) are driving each other crazy. Forced together by their dating parents, these two bitter enemies have alienated â or otherwise disposed of â most of their social circle, leaving them with plenty of quality time for each other. They go camping, start a business, form a band, join a team, try to make some new friends (including icky new characters Crustache and Lumpy Noodle) and engage in a "holy war." Things go from worse to worst, though, when the two boys find a cat â or is it a bird? â one hot summer day in the harrowing 51-page story "Blue Jay" (as previously serialized at Fantagraphics.com).

Steven Weissman, modern master of light tragedy, is at his most horrible with Chocolate Cheeks. Juxtaposing gag-driven, newspaper-fashioned strips that are just gross enough to delight younger readers and sophisticated enough to be appreciated by grown-ups alongside the symbolically rich extended narrative of "Blue Jay," this is the greatest "Yikes" book yet.
